goals.question: What is the average yield of barley across all varieties and sites?
goals.rationale: A box plot can show the median, quartiles, and outliers of the yield distribution, giving an idea of the central tendency and spread of the data.

goals.question: Which variety of barley has the highest yield on average?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of yield by variety
goals.rationale: A bar chart can show the differences in yield between the different varieties, making it easy to identify which one has the highest average yield.

goals.question: How does the yield of barley vary across different sites?
goals.visualization: Box plot of yield by site
goals.rationale: A box plot can show the differences in yield between the different sites, making it easy to identify which one has the highest or lowest yield on average.

goals.question: Is there a significant difference in yield between the two years in the dataset?
goals.visualization: Box plot of yield by year
goals.rationale: A box plot can show the differences in yield between the two years, making it easy to identify if there is a significant difference in yield between them.

goals.question: What is the distribution of yield for each variety?
goals.rationale: A histogram can show the distribution of yield for each variety, making it easy to identify if there are any differences in the shape or spread of the distributions.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(data['yield'])
    ax.set_title('What is the average yield of barley across all varieties and sites?')
    ax.set_ylabel('Yield')
    ax.set_xticklabels(['Barley'])
    plt.axhline(data['yield'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['yield'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    avg_yield_by_variety = data.groupby('variety')['yield'].mean()
    max_avg_yield = avg_yield_by_variety.max()
    max_variety = avg_yield_by_variety.idxmax()

    ax = avg_yield_by_variety.plot(kind='bar', color='c')
    plt.axhline(y=max_avg_yield, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Max Avg Yield: {max_avg_yield:.2f}')
    plt.title('Which variety of barley has the highest yield on average?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Variety')
    plt.ylabel('Average Yield')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='site', y='yield', data=data)
    plt.title('How does the yield of barley vary across different sites?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Site')
    plt.ylabel('Yield')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Site', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column='yield', by='year', ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('Is there a significant difference in yield between the two years in the dataset?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Yield')
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.legend(title='Year', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='yield', hue='variety', kde=True, bins=20, alpha=0.5)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of yield for each variety?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Yield')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(title='Variety', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
